==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Butteris
<hw>But"ter*is</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The same word as
<ets>buttress</ets>, noun, in a different application, F.
<ets>bouter</ets> to push.]</ety> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A steel cutting
instrument, with a long bent shank set in a handle which rests against
the shoulder of the operator. It is operated by a thrust movement, and
used in paring the hoofs of horses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Butterman</ent>⟦br⟧
